      <description><![CDATA[Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com or contact inquiries@nextanimation.com.tw to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEAn eruption from Bali's Mount Agung volcano is imminent. Authorities have evacuated some 75,000 people in danger zones surrounding areas.The volcano has been quiet for almost five decades, but last week 700 tremors were detected in a single day.  Experts, as well as the Indonesian government believe this to be a sign that Mount Agung is ready to erupt.The last time Mount Agung erupted was in 1963, and the resulting catastrophe killed more than 1,000 people.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location of volcano, danger zone and Denpasar city2. Cross section of volcano with magma rising3. Depiction of eruption at Mount Agung4. Depiction of gas after eruption5. Scale of Mount Agung against world's tallest building, Burj Khalifa6. A depiction of Balinese onlookers observing the 1963 Mount Agung eruption.VOICEOVER (in English): "The Indonesian island of Bali is home to some 4.2 million people.""Authorities have evacuated some 75,000 people in danger zones surrounding the Mt Agung volcano."30 miles southwest of it is the island's capital, Denpasar, as well as a busy international airport""The volcano has been quiet for almost five decades, but last week 700 tremors were detected in a single day. "Experts, as well as the Indonesian government believe this to be a sign that Mount Agung is ready to erupt.""If it does erupt, the resulting current of super-heated gas, known as a pyroclastic flow would pose a danger to anyone nearby ""Mount Agung stands at over 3,100 meters tall. That's more than 4 times the size of the  world's tallest building the Burj Khalifa.""However, any resulting ash cloud from an eruption could stretch to heights of 10,000 m or higher.""The last time Mount Agung erupted was in 1963, and the resulting catastrophe killed more than 1,000 people."SOURCES: Channel News Asia, Magma, The Guardian, BBChttp://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/once-tremors-detected-bali-volcano-can-erupt-within-hours-9269148https://magma.vsi.esdm.go.id/vona/display.php?noticenumber=2017AGU10https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/sep/27/bali-volcano-will-mount-agung-erupt-and-what-happens-if-it-doeshttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-41395831***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
