      <description><![CDATA[Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com or contact inquiries@nextanimation.com.tw to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEThe aircraft carrier USS Nimitz arrived in the Pacific on Tuesday, bringing the number of carriers to three now operating in the region. The carrier and its accompanying strike group of destroyers, cruisers and submarines has joined the U.S. Navy's 7th Fleet area of operations, the Navy said news releases, CNN reported. The Nimitz now joins the USS Ronald Reagan, which is stationed in Japan year-round, and the USS Theodore Roosevelt, which is currently far east of Japan, according to Business Insider. The Navy reported that the Nimitz just finished three months of in the Middle East battling ISIS, launching 1,322 sorties with 903 pieces of ordnance dropped, according to Military.com.Navy spokeswoman Lt. Mary Walsh described the carrier's activities as standard, and said that the Nimitz would only be in the region temporarily, Military.com reported.  The USS Roosevelt is expected to eventually take the Nimitz's place in the Middle East, according to CNN. Pyongyang hasn't launched a missile in over a month, however tensions still remain high in the region.    RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. The USS Nimitz sailing through the water2. The US now has 3 aircraft carriers in the Pacific3. The USS Nimitz was previously out in the Middle East4. Aircraft launching from the USS NimitzVOICEOVER (in English): "The aircraft carrier USS Nimitz arrived in the Pacific on Tuesday, bringing the number of carriers to three now operating in the region." "The carrier now joins the USS Ronald Reagan, which is stationed in Japan year-round, and the USS Theodore Roosevelt, which is currently far east of Japan.""According to the Navy, the Nimitz just finished three months of in the Middle East battling ISIS, launching 1,322 sorties and dropping 903 pieces of ordnance.""The Navy described the carrier's activities as standard, and said that the Nimitz would only be in the region temporarily."SOURCES: CNN, Business Insider, Military.comhttp://edition.cnn.com/2017/10/25/politics/us-navy-three-aircraft-carriers-pacific/index.htmlhttp://www.businessinsider.com/us-navy-third-aircraft-carrier-north-korea-pacific-2017-10http://www.military.com/daily-news/2017/10/25/rare-show-force-navy-now-three-carriers-pacific.html***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
