      <title>What is superfetation?</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com or contact inquiries@nextanimation.com.tw to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEA California woman reportedly conceived while pregnant in a extremely case of superfetation.During pregnancy, a woman's body stops producing eggs but in some extremely rare cases eggs are still produced after one has been fertilized.This is called superfetation. In reported cases, this is where a woman conceives another child while already pregnant.Unlike a twin pregnancy, superfetation is when two fetuses grow separately inside the same woman at different rates.In 2009, a doctor speaking to ABC in 2009 about a case of superfetation, said she could only find 10 cases of it in medical literature.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Egg production while pregnant2. Sperm fertilizing egg3. Inside the womb4. Statistics on superfetationVOICEOVER (in English): "During pregnancy, a woman's body stops producing eggs but in some extremely rare cases eggs are still produced after one has been fertilized." "This is called superfetation. In reported cases, this is where a woman conceives another child while already pregnant."  "Unlike a twin pregnancy, superfetation is when two fetuses grow separately inside the same woman at different rates." "In 2009, a doctor speaking to ABC in 2009 about a case of superfetation, said she could only find 10 cases of it in medical literature."SOURCES: New York Post, Sacramento Bee (Washington Post), ABChttp://nypost.com/2017/10/25/i-rented-out-my-womb-and-they-took-my-own-son/http://www.sacbee.com/latest-news/article181563751.htmlhttp://abcnews.go.com/Health/ReproductiveHealth/pregnant-woman-pregnant-julia-grovenburg-conceives-consecutively/story?id=8656369***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Lat